The platform is the rest api service.

Pre-request:
1. The platform cannot be run out of Jetty:
   mvn clean install jetty:run
2. To run it under eclipse:
1) Right click Debug Configuration
2) Select Maven Build and option for new
3) Name it for anything
4) Under the Main tab, Base Directory is /home/jassica/Yummet/Yummet/Webapp/app/v1/core/platform   Goals set to "jetty:run"

User Service Descrption (Example can be found under RestUserServiceTest)
1. http://localhost:8080/api/users/userUpsert
Input: Should be a json object for the UserObject where the lastModifiedDate, CreatedDate, Id should leave empty. Example is 
	{\"id\": \"1\", \"firstName\": \"Tom\",\"lastName\": \"Cruise\",\"email\": \"ycwmike@gmai.com\", \"photo\": \"Object or null (paramter decide)\", \"phone\": \"1234567\",\"creditInfo\": \"1231231\",\"activeScore\": \"123112321\",\"alias\": \"alias\",\"role\": \"admin\", \"sessionExpire\": \"2012-12-24T21:20:47.668+0000\",\"password\": \"afadsfdafa(hash value)\",\"newpassword\": \"adfafdafadfdf\"}
Output: Return the UserObject with all the required fields set. Like the created Date will be automatically filled in

2. http://localhost:8080/api/users/userDelete
Input: Should be a json object for the UserObject but we only care the Id in this call
Output: Return a message with code as Json Object

3. http://localhost:8080/api/users/userQueryx/{emailOfUser}
Input: Need include User Email under the path
Output: Json object for the user

Post Service Descrption (Example can be found under RestPostServiceTest)
1. http://localhost:8080/api/posts/providePostUpsert
Input: Should be a json object for the ProvidePostObject where the lastModifiedDate, CreatedDate, Id should leave empty. Example is 
	{ \"subject\": \"Test Food Post\","
				+ "\"creator\":{\"id\":\"1\",\"email\": \"ycwmike@gmai.com\" }, \"lastModifiedBy\":{\"id\":\"1\",\"email\": \"ycwmike@gmai.com\" },  "
				+ "\"location\": \"San Francisco\",\"quantity\": \"7\",\"commentsOrDescription\": \"Test Food\", "
				+ "\"cost\": \"10.09\", \"postCategory\": \"Food\",\"status\": \"Open\",\"visibility\": \"p\", "
				+ "\"expireDate\": \"2012-12-24T21:20:47.668+0000\"
Output: Return the ProvidePostObject with all the required fields set. Like the created Date will be automatically filled in

2. http://localhost:8080/api/posts/providePostDelete
Input: Should be a json object for the ProvidePostObject but we only care the Id in this call
Output: Return a message with code as Json Object

3. http://localhost:8080/api/posts/providePostQueryx/{IdOfPostObject}
Input: Need include ProvidePostObject id under the path
Output: Json object for the ProvidePostObject

4. http://localhost:8080/api/posts/providePostLimitQuery/{userEmail}/{startIndex}/{numberOfPosts}
Input: All the information should be included under path
Output: Json object for all the retrieved ProvidePostObjects
Example: ycwmike@gmai.com/1/3 means
Get 3 ProvidePostObject created by ycwmike@gmai.com but skip the latest 1 post

